parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Unwanted ABS activation can cause the vehicle to lose braking power, leading to increased stopping distances, accidents, and potential injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The ABS system activates at low speeds
causing the brakes to pulsate or grab
and making it difficult to stop the vehicle. This can occur on dry pavement

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Brake failure can cause accidents, injuries, or fatalities, especially if the vehicle is traveling at high speeds or in heavy traffic.
symptoms: The brakes fail to stop the vehicle
or the brake pedal feels soft or spongy. In some cases
the brake lights may come on
and the vehicle may experience a loss of braking power.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Electrical system failures can cause a range of problems, including brake failure, ABS malfunctions, and other safety issues.
symptoms: or the vehicle experiences electrical issues
such as faulty oxygen sensors or catalytic converters.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Tire tread separation and failure can cause loss of vehicle control, accidents, and injuries.
symptoms: bubbles on the side of the tire

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Spare tire cracking and failure can cause loss of vehicle control, accidents, and injuries when the spare tire is used.
symptoms: Deep cracks on the sidewall of the spare tire

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure to honor tire warranties can cause financial burden and inconvenience to vehicle owners.
The failure of the electrical system can cause the vehicle to shut off or stall, leading to loss of power steering and brakes, and potentially resulting in accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: loss of power steering and brakes

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition switch and anti-theft system can cause the vehicle to not start or stall, leading to inconvenience and potential safety risks.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Brake Light and Turn Signal Switch Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake light and turn signal switch can cause accidents or reduce visibility, leading to potential safety risks.

and check gauge light stays on.
